  "doi": null,
  "abstract": "We apply a tag-and-probe method to precisely measure the absolute branching fraction of the decay $η_c \\to γγ$ with the BESIII experiment at BEPCII. Starting with a large initial sample of $2712.4\\pm 14.3$ million $ψ(3686)$ events, a sample of 0.16 million $η_c$ events are tagged via the golden channel $ψ(3686)\\to π^0 h_c$, $h_c\\to γη_c$, effectively avoiding interference effects. The absolute branching fraction of $η_c \\to γγ$ is measured for the first time to be $\\mathcal{B}(η_c \\to γγ) = (2.45 \\pm 0.48_{\\rm stat.} \\pm 0.09_{\\rm syst.}) \\times 10^{-4}$. Using the world average value of the total width of the $η_c$, the partial decay width of $η_c \\to γγ$ is calculated to be $Γ(η_c \\to γγ) = (7.48 \\pm 1.48_{\\rm stat.} \\pm 0.30_{\\rm syst.})~{\\rm keV}$.",
